            [
                'title' => 'The Comeback Kid',
                'content' => "At 35, I was bankrupt, divorced, and living in my parents' basement. Everything I'd built had crumbled. Friends stopped calling. I stopped believing in myself.\n\nMy father, a man of few words, sat with me one night. \"You're not done,\" he said. \"You're just getting started again.\"\n\nI didn't believe him. But I started anyway. I took a minimum wage job. I paid off one debt at a time. I rebuilt my credit, my confidence, my life—one tiny step after another.\n\nTen years later, I'm running a successful consulting firm. My father's words hang framed in my office: \"You're not done. You're just getting started again.\"",
                'excerpt' => 'From bankruptcy and divorce to business success—one step at a time.',
                'category' => 'inspiration',
                'author_type' => AuthorType::Self,
                'tags' => ['comeback', 'failure', 'family', 'business'],
