            [
                'title' => 'Painting in the Dark',
                'content' => "When I lost my sight at 52, I thought my life as an artist was over. How could I paint what I couldn't see?\n\nBut art wouldn't let me go. I started experimenting with texture, with raised canvases I could feel. I mixed colors from memory, trusting my hands to know what my eyes no longer could.\n\nMy first \"blind\" painting sold at a gallery showing. The buyer said it was the most emotionally powerful piece she'd ever seen.\n\n\"You painted with your soul,\" she told me. \"I can feel everything you couldn't see.\"\n\nLosing my sight didn't end my art. It transformed it into something deeper.",
                'excerpt' => 'Blindness couldn\'t stop an artist\'s creative spirit.',
