            // GRATITUDE (12 stories)
            [
                'title' => 'The Gift of Ordinary Days',
                'content' => "After my cancer diagnosis, everything changed. Not just the obvious things—the treatments, the fear, the uncertainty. What changed most was how I saw my regular Tuesday mornings.\n\nBefore cancer, I'd rush through breakfast, annoyed at traffic, stressed about deadlines. Now I linger over my coffee. I notice how the light comes through the kitchen window. I call my mother just to hear her voice.\n\nI'm in remission now, but I never want to forget what cancer taught me: there is no such thing as an ordinary day. Every boring, routine, unremarkable moment is a gift we're not guaranteed.",
                'excerpt' => 'Cancer taught her to treasure the ordinary moments.',
