                'content' => "I used to resent my difficult childhood. The poverty, the instability, the things other kids had that I didn't. It took me years of therapy to see it differently.\n\nThose hard years taught me resilience. They showed me what truly matters. They gave me empathy for others who struggle. Every obstacle I overcame added to my strength.\n\nI'm not grateful that bad things happened. I'm grateful for who I became because of them. There's a difference—and finding it changed my entire relationship with my past.",
                'excerpt' => 'Finding gratitude not for hardship, but for growth through hardship.',
