                'title' => 'My Mother\'s Hands',
                'content' => "I was helping my mother in the kitchen when I really noticed her hands for the first time. Wrinkled now, spotted with age, but still so capable.\n\nThose hands changed my diapers and packed my school lunches. They applauded at my recitals and wiped my tears. They held mine through every hard moment and every joyful one.\n\nI reached over and took her hand in mine. \"Thank you,\" I said. She looked confused. \"For what?\"\n\n\"For everything your hands have done for me.\"\n\nShe squeezed my hand back, and we stood there in the kitchen, connected by something deeper than words.",
                'excerpt' => 'A moment of gratitude for a mother\'s lifelong care.',
