                'title' => 'Grateful for My Body',
                'content' => "I spent decades at war with my body. Too fat, too slow, too imperfect. I criticized every curve, every flaw, every limitation.\n\nThen my body carried me through cancer treatment. It fought when I couldn't. It healed when I had no hope left. It kept showing up for me even when I'd spent years being cruel to it.\n\nNow I look in the mirror differently. Thank you, body, for being strong when I was weak. Thank you for healing. Thank you for being mine.\n\nI'm done fighting you. From now on, we're on the same team.",
                'excerpt' => 'Illness transformed her relationship with her body.',
                'category' => 'gratitude',
