            [
                'title' => 'The Neighbor Who Noticed',
                'content' => "When my husband died, I disappeared. I stopped leaving the house, stopped answering the phone, stopped eating regular meals.\n\nMy neighbor Margaret noticed. She didn't push or pry. She just started leaving dinner on my porch every evening. A pot of soup. A casserole. A plate of cookies.\n\nThose meals saved me. Not just nutritionally—emotionally. Knowing someone saw me, cared about me, thought of me every single day. It was a lifeline I didn't know I needed.\n\nThank you, Margaret. Your consistency kept me alive long enough to want to live again.",
                'excerpt' => 'A neighbor\'s daily kindness became a lifeline through grief.',
                'category' => 'gratitude',
                'author_type' => AuthorType::Self,
                'tags' => ['grief', 'neighbors', 'kindness', 'widow'],
