            [
                'title' => 'Finding Gratitude in Pain',
                'content' => "My chronic pain taught me something unexpected: how to appreciate the moments between.\n\nWhen the pain is bad, everything shrinks to survival. But when it eases, even slightly, I feel genuine joy. A moment without pain becomes precious. A day of mild discomfort feels like victory.\n\nI've learned to celebrate what I used to ignore. A morning where I can make breakfast. An afternoon where I can take a short walk. An evening without tears.\n\nPain taught me that gratitude isn't about having everything. It's about noticing what you do have—especially on the hard days.",
                'excerpt' => 'Chronic pain revealed a deeper kind of gratitude.',
                'category' => 'gratitude',
