            [
                'title' => 'The Anonymous Scholarship',
                'content' => "I almost didn't go to college. My family had no money, and loans felt impossible. Then I received a letter: I'd been awarded a full scholarship from an anonymous donor.\n\nI never learned who paid for my education. I wrote thank you letters to the scholarship office, hoping they'd be passed along. I graduated with honors. I became a doctor.\n\nTwenty years later, I set up my own anonymous scholarship fund. Somewhere out there, students are receiving the same mysterious gift I did. The kindness keeps circling.\n\nTo my unknown benefactor: you changed my life. I'm paying it forward forever.",
                'excerpt' => 'An anonymous donor\'s generosity created a legacy of giving.',
                'category' => 'kindness',
                'author_type' => AuthorType::Self,
                'tags' => ['education', 'scholarship', 'generosity', 'paying-it-forward'],
            ],
            [
                'title' => 'The Grocery Store Guardian',
                'content' => "I was in the grocery checkout with my three kids, exhausted and frazzled. My card was declined. I didn't have another one.\n\nI started putting items back, trying not to cry, trying to figure out which things we could live without. My kids were confused and upset.\n\nThe woman behind me stepped forward. \"I've got it,\" she said quietly. The whole bill—$150.\n\nI tried to get her information, to pay her back somehow. She refused. \"I've been where you are,\" she said. \"Just help someone else someday.\"\n\nI have. Many times. Her kindness taught me that we rise by lifting others.",
                'excerpt' => 'A stranger\'s generosity in a moment of embarrassment.',
